y, his conception of religion, and the role of his choral odes.Assuming no specialized knowledge, Ritual Irony is aimed at all readers of Euripidean tragedy. It will prove particularly valuable to students and scholars of classics, comparative literature, and symbolic anthropology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aDidactic drama, GreekxHistory and criticism. 0aIrony in literature. 0aMythology, Greek, in literature. 0aRitual in literature. 0aSacrifice in literature. 0aTragedy. 4aPoetry & Criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook Package Archivez978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501740633zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501740633zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501740633.jpg  a978-3-11-053617-1 COR eBook Package Archive  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA